===Etymology 1===

An Italian simplification of the [[Greek]] name [[Ariadne]] ("most  holy"; Cretan Greek ''αρι'' (ari) "most" and ''αδνος'' (adnos) "holy").

====Proper noun====
{{en-proper noun}}
#{{given name|female|from Greek|}} A female [[given name]].

===Etymology 2===
A [[Welsh]] name meaning "silver" (derived from Welsh ''arian'', "silver").

====Proper noun====
{{en-proper noun}}
#{{given name|female|from Welsh|}} A female [[given name]].

===Etymology 3===
From Persian, signifying that the person was born in [[Aryan]] territory (the Persian Empire, including Afghnistan, Pakistan, and some parts of India).

====Proper noun====
{{en-proper noun}}
#{{given name|female|from Persian|}} A female [[given name]].

